Gemini said*Streamline Your Cash: New COD Reports*







We are introducing two new business-critical reports in COD Management to
provide better visibility into COD collections, online payment settlements,
and reconciliation flows. These reports help businesses track COD orders,
rider and admin collected payments, monitor transfer and settlement
statuses, and simplify financial operations for accounts using T+1
remittance.


Why We Built This?




Businesses required deeper visibility into how Cash on Delivery (COD)
payments are collected, transferred, and settled across riders, admins, and
bank accounts. These new reports help reduce reconciliation effort and
improve operational financial tracking.
What=E2=80=99s NewCOD Orders Collection Report


Available under: *COD Management =E2=86=92 Get Report*


Key Additions:

   -

   COD collection bifurcation based on *Payment Mode*
   -

   Tracks order settlement lifecycle from delivery to bank settlement
   -

   Visibility into:
   -

      Transaction Date/ID
      -

      Transfer Date/ID
      -

      Settlement Date/ID
      -

   Rider and Network level tracking
   -

   Standardized settlement remarks


Online Settlement Report


Available only for accounts with *T+1 Remittance enabled*


Key Additions:

   -

   Dedicated tracking for online payment settlements processed via T+1
   -

   Supports filtering at both the Admin and Rider levels since online
   payment can be done by either.
   -

   Complete visibility into:
   -

      Transaction Date/ID
      -

      Transfer Date/ID
      -

      Settlement Date/ID
      -

   Settlement reconciliation tracking for next-day remittance flows

What This Means To YouGemini said




   -

   Faster and more accurate financial reconciliation
   -

   Better visibility into COD and online payment settlements
   -

   Easier tracking of rider/admin collected payments
   -

   Improved monitoring of T+1 remittance processing
   -

   Reduced dependency on manual settlement validation

What=E2=80=99s Next

Something exciting is coming soon - Stay tuned !!
